# Networking in Docker 

>Bridge ,docker run ubuntu
>none ,docker run ubuntu --network=none
>host ,docker run ubuntu --network=host

## bridge network ,private internal network create by docker on host.internally ips ,i.e 172.17 ,can access each other using internal ip ,for outside world map port.

## host network ,then can access outside or internal ,same port .

## none ,isolated network not connected to any network ,so can't access outside.

>> by default docker creates only one internal network in bridge network containers.

>docker network create \ --driver bridge \ --subnet 182.18.0.0/16 custom-isolated-network . custom internal network.

>>docker network ls >list all networks .

>>docker inspect conID, networks key,ip add.

## all containers on host ,a builtin dns server runs on 127.0.0.11 ,helps resolve each other using container name.

>>create namespaces to create container and connect via virtual ethernet cable.